Package: BayesMRclus
Type: Package
Title: Bayesian Hierarchical Modeling for Two-Sample Summary-Data Mendelian Randomization under Heterogeneity
Version: 0.0.6-6
Date: 2026-01-02
Authors@R: c(
  person("Sergio", "Venturini", role=c("aut", "cre"), email = "sergio.venturini@unicatt.it"),
  person("Guido", "Consonni", role=c("ctb"), email = "guido.consonni@unicatt.it"),
  person("Federico", "Castelletti", role=c("ctb"), email = "federico.castelletti@unicatt.it"))
Description: Functions to perform inference in a Bayesian setting for two-sample summary-data
  Mendelian randomization (MR) design with and without clustering of the genetic variants
  (i.e. the instrumental variables) included in the analysis.
